object.script:
-- 23-gear near-CV manual transmission representing all meaningful -- gear combinations from two 7-speed gearbox units connected in series. -- For use as a dyno component for calibrating gear ratios -- Or make it an automatic transmission and submit me your branch of development. -- It shouldn't take much. -- -- Levitator
gear_array={ {1,1}, -- x1 {1,2}, -- x1.2 {2,2}, -- x1.44 {1,3}, -- x1.5 {1,4}, -- x1.8 {1,5}, -- x2 {2,4}, -- x2.16 {3,3}, -- x2.25 {2,5}, -- x2.4 {1,6}, -- x2.5 {3,4}, -- x2.7 {1,7}, -- x3 {4,4}, -- x3.24 {4,5}, -- x3.6 {3,6}, -- x3.75 {5,5}, -- x4 {4,6}, -- x4.5 {5,6}, -- x5 {4,7}, -- x5.4 {5,7}, -- x6 {6,6}, -- x6.25 {6,7}, -- x7.5 {7,7}, -- x9 }
function onTick() gear=math.floor(input.getNumber(1)) obj=gear_array[gear] if obj==nil then obj=gear_array[1] end output.setNumber(1, obj[1] ) output.setNumber(2, obj[2] ) end
function onDraw() end

object.script:
-- Track the rate of battery and fuel consumption -- Display the rate and duration remaining for each in minutes
function gn(n) return input.getNumber(n) end
function sn(n,v) output.setNumber(n,v) end
function state_obj() return {prev=0,cur=0,rate=0} end
updateticks=120 -- Ticks between updates, 60/sec batstate=state_obj() fuelstate=state_obj()
function update(state,v) state.prev=state.cur state.cur=v state.rate=(state.cur-state.prev) * updateticks / 60 -- Track rate in d/sec end
clock=0 function onTick() clock=clock+1 fuel=gn(1) bat=gn(2)*100
if clock>=updateticks then update(fuelstate,fuel) update(batstate,bat) clock=0 end sn(1,fuelstate.rate) sn(2,fuel/fuelstate.rate) sn(3,batstate.rate) sn(4,bat/batstate.rate) end
posx=property.getNumber("Pos X") posy=property.getNumber("Pos Y") function timestr(sec) if sec>=math.huge or sec<=-math.huge then return "--:--:--" else return string.format("%02.0f:%02.0f:%02.0f",sec/3600,(sec/60)%60,sec%60) end end
function onDraw() local str=string.format("BAT : %3.0f%% %+5.2f\n" .. "T : %s\n" .. "FUEL: %4.0fL %+2.2f\n" .. "T : %s\n" .. "RATES/MIN", bat,batstate.rate*60,timestr(-bat/batstate.rate), fuel,fuelstate.rate*60,timestr(-fuel/fuelstate.rate)) screen.setColor(0,0,153) screen.drawText(posx,posy,str) end

object.script:
function gn(x) return input.getNumber(x) end
function gb(x) return input.getBool(x) end
function onTick() clutch=gb(1) bat=gn(2) temp=gn(3) speed=gn(5) rpm=gn(6) gear=gn(7) end
colw=5 rowh=6
function gear_name(x) if x==0 then return "N" elseif x==-1 then return "R" else return string.format("%.0f",x) end end
function rg(bool) local c={0,255}
if bool then c[1]=255 c[2]=0 end screen.setColor(c[1],c[2],0) end
function onDraw()
local str
w=screen.getWidth() h=screen.getHeight()
str=string.format("%5.0f KPH\n%5.0f RPM", speed, rpm) screen.setColor(0,255,0) screen.drawTextBox(0,0,w,rowh,str)
rg(temp>95) screen.drawTextBox(0,rowh*2,w,rowh,string.format("%3.2f C",temp))
rg(bat<25) screen.drawTextBox(0,rowh*3,w,rowh,string.format("%3.2f BAT",bat))
screen.setColor(0,255,0) screen.drawTextBox(0,rowh*4,w,rowh,string.format("GEAR %s",gear_name(gear)))
if clutch then screen.setColor(255,0,0) end screen.drawTextBox(colw*7,rowh*4,w,rowh,"CLUTCH")
end
